Key Match Events: Edson Álvarez scored a 101st-minute goal to save Mexico.
Mexico won an absurd penalty shootout.
Luis Chávez scored a late-first-half free kick.
Santi Giménez and Luis Malagón helped Mexico take a lead in the penalty shootout.
César Huerta missed twice but scored on the third attempt in the penalty shootout.
Andy Najar missed for Honduras in the penalty shootout.
Post-Match Reflections: Mexico qualified for the 2024 Copa América.
The victory was seen as crucial for ticket and merchandise sales for the 2024 Nations League finals.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played at Estadio Azteca in Mexico City.
There were conspiracy theories about the added stoppage time.
Honduran keeper Edrick Menjivar was penalized for stepping off his line during the shootout.
